coration: underline;\">Funding Raising/Bake Sale</span></strong>\r\n\r\nLast week, kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) had free sample for her homemade 蜂蜜蛋糕. For those who had one or two or even more, you knew that\'s very delicious. Will inform you when she plans to have bake sale next time.\r\n\r\nThis Saturday (10/30) 黃勤珍(Chinchen Burkholder) will have 京餅, 豬肉餡餅, 芝麻甜餅. and Mrs. Xiao yu Shia  will have her homemade bake sale. Due to the Halloween Event, we will have this sale out side the parent lounge.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Lost and Found</span></strong>\r\n\r\nIf you left two Martha Stewart \"living\" magazine at parents lounge last week, please let me know.\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newletter -10/30/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newletter-10302010','','','2010-10-28 12:22:23','2010-10-28 16:22:23','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=104',0,'post','',0),(105,1,'2010-10-28 12:21:43','2010-10-28 16:21:43','MCS Newsletter                                        Oct.30, 2010\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\n\nWe will have our 2010 Halloween Parade on October 30 during the recess. All students are encouraged to wear their costumes to school. Just a reminder, no bloody make up, weapon or mask, because we have students at younger age. We will have parents lounge as event location and room will be closed from 1:00 pm till parade is over. Sorry for the inconvenient.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising/Bake Sale</span></strong>\n\nLast week, kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) had free sample for her homemade 蜂蜜蛋糕. For those who had one or two or even more, you knew that\'s very delicious. Will inform you when she plans to have bake sale next time.\n\nThis Saturday (10/30) 黃勤珍(Chinchen Burkholder) will have 京餅, 豬肉餡餅, 芝麻甜餅. and Mrs. Xiao yu Shia  will have her homemade bake sale. Due to the Halloween Event, we will have this sale out side the parent lounge.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Lost and Found</span></strong>\n\nIf you left two Martha Stewart \"living\" magazine at parents lounge last week, please let me know.','MCS Newletter -10/30/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','104-revision','','','2010-10-28 12:21:43','2010-10-28 16:21:43','',104,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=105',0,'revision','',0),(106,1,'2010-11-05 22:02:42','2010-11-06 02:02:42','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had her bake sale last week and donated all money to school.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to all staff and parents, we had a wonderful Halloween party.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Did you know all the bats in different size on window blinds were hand made by 陳俐君(Tracy Wu) ?</li>\r\n	<li>Did you notice some pumpkins were smoking? That\'s special dry ice effect provided by   呂思平(Szuping Lu).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAlso we had many hand carved pumpkins on display.\r\n\r\nWe spent a little, but enjoyed A LOT. The event expense meets our budget. Once again, thanks to staff and parents who helped to decorate the parent lounge and clean up at the end. Also thanks to staff and parents who stood in the aisle to distribute candy to students and this event can\'t be succeeded without your support.\r\n\r\nAll event pictures are available on school website under \"Album\" or follow the link below.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we want to hear from you about the teaching environment/style for your child/children, we will have teachers survey soon. Each parent rep. will hand out a hard copy of survey form to each parent. Please sit down with your child, go over the form and fill it out. We believe there is always room for improvement and would like to have proper communication channel between parents/students and teacher.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Parents Rep. /Staff Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis Saturday (11/6), all staff and parent rep. from each class are invited to attend.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Location: Parents Lounge Room 2423/2425</li>\r\n	<li>Meeting Start Time: 1:40 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\n波霸奶茶- provided by kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky). All sale will 100% donate to school.','MCS Newsletter Nov.6, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-6-2010','','','2010-11-05 22:02:42','2010-11-06 02:02:42','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=106',0,'post','',0),(107,1,'2010-11-05 22:01:55','2010-11-06 02:01:55','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had her bake sale last week and donated all money to school.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\n\nThanks to all staff and parents, we had a wonderful Halloween party.\n<ul>\n	<li>Did you know all the bats in different size on window blinds were hand made by 陳俐君(Tracy Wu) ?</li>\n	<li>Did you notice some pumpkins were smoking? That\'s special dry ice effect provided by   呂思平(Szuping Lu).</li>\n</ul>\nAlso we had many hand carved pumpkins on display.\n\nWe spent a little, but enjoyed A LOT. The event expense meets our budget. Once again, thanks to staff and parents who helped to decorate the parent lounge and clean up at the end. Also thanks to staff and parents who stood in the aisle to distribute candy to students and this event can\'t be succeeded without your support.\n\nAll event pictures are available on school website under \"Album\" or follow the link below.\n\n<a href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/MichiganChineseSchool/Halloween2010</a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nBecause we want to hear from you about the teaching environment/style for your child/children, we will have teachers survey soon. Each parent rep. will hand out a hard copy of survey form to each parent. Please sit down with your child, go over the form and fill it out. We believe there is always room for improvement and would like to have proper communication channel between parents/students and teacher.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Parents Rep. /Staff Meeting</span></strong>\n\nThis Saturday (11/6), all staff and parent rep. from each class are invited to attend.\n<ul>\n	<li>Location: Parents Lounge Room 2423/2425</li>\n	<li>Meeting Start Time: 1:40 pm</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n\n波霸奶茶- provided by kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky). All sale will 100% donate to school.','MCS Newsletter Nov.6, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','106-revision','','','2010-11-05 22:01:55','2010-11-06 02:01:55','',106,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=107',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2010-11-12 00:20:19','2010-11-12 04:20:19','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Thanks to 唐宗堯, 張子若 (Alex and Joanne Tang) donation to Michigan Chinese School.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Thanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising. She had波霸奶茶 sale last week and donated all money to school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThe survey forms had been given to parent rep. last Saturday and all parents should receive one. If you don\'t have it, make sure contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. Please return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. This is an anonymous survey, but you need to list the class/grade.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 New Year Party Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMeeting was held last week. Below is brief summary:\r\n\r\nLocation: Stevenson High School\r\n\r\nTime:  2:30 – 8:00 pm\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDirectory is completed and will be available this Saturday. Please stop by Parents Lounge during regular school hour to pick up.\r\n\r\nHunan Hunan will be on campus this Saturday.',' MCS Newsletter         Nov.13, 20',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-13-20','','','2010-11-12 00:20:19','2010-11-12 04:20:19','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=108',0,'post','',0),(109,1,'2010-11-12 00:19:46','2010-11-12 04:19:46','',' MCS Newsletter         Nov.13, 20',0,'','inherit','open','open','','108-revision','','','2010-11-12 00:19:46','2010-11-12 04:19:46','',108,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=109',0,'revision','',0),(110,1,'2010-11-19 08:47:37','2010-11-19 12:47:37','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising last week.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe want to hear your voice by anonymous survey. If you don\'t have survey form, make sure to contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. </span>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDirectory is ready and available to pick up during regular school hour at parents lounge. Thanks to賴昭宇 (Jauyeu Lai) hard work to make school directory in time for delivery. Do you notice we have very good quality on directory paper and a transparent cover? Higher quality, but lower expense.\r\n\r\nIf you are going to have business with those advertisement sponsors on our directory, Please mention you saw their advertisement on Michigan Chinese School directory and thanks their support.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>QQ bakery this week. Due to popular demand, we have increase our bakery order from last time. Hope everyone can enjoy and support this event.</li>\r\n	<li>Walnut pumpkin pie by 林曉君(Vicky) – limited quantity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Thanksgiving</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Soon Thanksgiving will become the focus of our attention. The upcoming seasons allow us to celebrate the most valuable gifts we have been given---those of love, family, friends, health, peace, and the opportunity to give thanks and to share our gifts with one another.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>There will be no school on Nov. 27. </strong></li>\r\n</ul>','MCS Newsletter    Nov.20, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-nov-20-2010','','','2010-11-19 08:47:37','2010-11-19 12:47:37','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=110',0,'post','',0),(111,1,'2010-11-19 08:47:35','2010-11-19 12:47:35','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky) fund raising last week.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe want to hear your voice by anonymous survey. If you don\'t have survey form, make sure to contact your parent rep. Please sit down with your child, go over the survey and fill it out. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Return the completed survey no later than 11/20 to your parent rep. </span>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month started on Oct. 30 and will be ended on Dec. 4. Please encourage your child/children to read as much Chinese material as he/she can.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 Directory</span></strong>\n\nDirectory is ready and available to pick up during regular school hour at parents lounge. Thanks to賴昭宇 (Jauyeu Lai) hard work to make school directory in time for delivery. Do you notice we have very good quality on directory paper and a transparent cover? Higher quality, but lower expense.\n\nIf you are going to have business with those advertisement sponsors on our directory, Please mention you saw their advertisement on Michigan Chinese School directory and thanks their support.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>QQ bakery this week. Due to popular demand, we have increase our bakery order from last time. Hope everyone can enjoy and support this event.</li>\n	<li>Walnut pumpkin pie by 林曉君(Vicky) – limited quantity</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Thanksgiving</span></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Soon Thanksgiving will become the focus of our attention. The upcoming seasons allow us to celebrate the most valuable gifts we have been given---those of love, family, friends, health, peace, and the opportunity to give thanks and to share our gifts with one another.</li>\n	<li><strong>There will be no school on Nov. 27. </strong></li>\n</ul>','MCS Newsletter    Nov.20, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','110-revision','','','2010-11-19 08:47:35','2010-11-19 12:47:35','',110,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=111',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2010-12-02 22:54:09','2010-12-03 02:54:09','MCS Newsletter                                        Dec. 4, 2010\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky)  pumpkin pies fund raising on Nov.20. Vicky has been running her bake  sale and donated all money to school for last four weeks.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe are collecting the survey from all classes and will review the result with each teacher individually.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month will be ended on Dec. 4. Please have student turn in his/her recording form to teacher this Saturday. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Late submission will not be accepted</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nPresenter: Joel Levi\r\n\r\nSubject: Pre-paid Legal Service\r\n\r\nDate: 12/4/2010\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45 PM\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nThe  presenter put an ad in our directory to support our school (see  attached).  Pre-paid Legal Service is a very new idea, kind of like  buying insurance for the legal services that we might need down the  road. We encourage parents to come to learn something new and also  support our advertiser.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">全球華文網」新闢「學生華語創作園地」</span></strong>\r\n\r\n為使全球華語文相關工作者及教師能分享華文教學經驗及心情故事，僑委會於本（99）年4月起辦理「全球華文網」之「我的華文故事」徵文活動，業獲致良好迴響。茲為使華語文學習者亦有發表作品及分享學習心得之場域，特自本年11月起在「我的華文故事」專區增闢「學生華語創作園地」專欄。鼓勵學子們踴躍投稿，前揭專欄網址請由「全球華文網」（<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.huayuworld.org</a>）首頁「我的華文故事」項下進入。\r\n\r\n相關聯結網址：<a href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760</a>','MCS Newsletter -12/4/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-1242010','','','2010-12-02 22:54:09','2010-12-03 02:54:09','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=112',0,'post','',0),(113,1,'2010-12-02 22:53:58','2010-12-03 02:53:58','MCS Newsletter                                        Dec. 4, 2010\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to kindergarten parent 林曉君(Vicky)  pumpkin pies fund raising on Nov.20. Vicky has been running her bake  sale and donated all money to school for last four weeks.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe are collecting the survey from all classes and will review the result with each teacher individually.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\n\nReading month will be ended on Dec. 4. Please have student turn in his/her recording form to teacher this Saturday. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Late submission will not be accepted</span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">.</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\n</span>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\n\nPresenter: Joel Levi\n\nSubject: Pre-paid Legal Service\n\nDate: 12/4/2010\n\nTime: 1:45 PM\n\nLocation: Parents Lounge\n\nThe  presenter put an ad in our directory to support our school (see  attached).  Pre-paid Legal Service is a very new idea, kind of like  buying insurance for the legal services that we might need down the  road. We encourage parents to come to learn something new and also  support our advertiser.\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">全球華文網」新闢「學生華語創作園地」</span></strong>\n\n為使全球華語文相關工作者及教師能分享華文教學經驗及心情故事，僑委會於本（99）年4月起辦理「全球華文網」之「我的華文故事」徵文活動，業獲致良好迴響。茲為使華語文學習者亦有發表作品及分享學習心得之場域，特自本年11月起在「我的華文故事」專區增闢「學生華語創作園地」專欄。鼓勵學子們踴躍投稿，前揭專欄網址請由「全球華文網」（<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.huayuworld.org</a>）首頁「我的華文故事」項下進入。\n\n相關聯結網址：<a href=\"http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.huayuworld.org/?p=9760</a>','MCS Newsletter -12/4/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','112-revision','','','2010-12-02 22:53:58','2010-12-03 02:53:58','',112,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=113',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2010-12-10 22:25:55','2010-12-11 02:25:55','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Jitai &amp; Long-Hua Jhou (周治太, 駱龍華) picked up the bakery from QQ on Nov.20.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be presented this week to each student who read more than 240 mins during reading month.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Presentation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a presentation about \"Pre-paid Legal Service\" last week and anyone who is interested can visit their website: <a title=\"blocked::http://www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour\" target=\"_blank\">www.prepaidlegal.com/hub/phasefour</a> and/or call direct at (877) 251-9472.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan  will be on campus this Saturday. You can order in advanced and pick up  at school hours. See contact information in 2010-2011 school directory  page A-9.','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 11, 2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-dec-11-2010','','','2010-12-10 22:25:55','2010-12-11 02:25:55','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=114',0,'post','',0),(115,1,'2010-12-10 22:25:13','2010-12-11 02:25:13','','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 11, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','114-revision','','','2010-12-10 22:25:13','2010-12-11 02:25:13','',114,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=115',0,'revision','',0),(116,1,'2010-12-16 18:10:45','2010-12-16 22:10:45','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Szuping Lu\'s(呂思平) dedicated hard work. With his family support, we have very creative and unique reading month award this year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Job Opportunity</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFord Powertrain Manufacturing Engineering has following jobs opening.\r\n\r\n1. Machining\r\n\r\n●Gears   ●Aluminum Machining   ●Tooling   ●Gauging\r\n\r\n2. Metallurgy\r\n\r\n3. Industrial / Plant Engineer\r\n\r\n●Industrial Engineer   ●Plant Layout   ●Material Handling\r\n\r\n4. Assembly and Test Engineer\r\n\r\nIf  you or you know of any talented people out there looking for work,  please direct them to the website to complete a career profile.\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings\" target=\"_blank\">http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings</a>:\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  have collected surveys from all classes and will review result with  each teacher individually to ensure the communication between teachers  and parents/students.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nQQ bakery this week.  Please remember 3<sup>rd</sup> week each month, we will have QQ bakery sale as our fund raising.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Your Support Makes All The Difference</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBecause  of support received from you and other generous individuals, we have  been able to make real progress toward furthering our important mission.\r\n\r\nFor upcoming year, there are several major events:\r\n\r\n(1)   January – 新年晚會\r\n\r\n(2)   April - 校內演講比賽\r\n\r\n<strong>(3) </strong>May -校際演講比賽 – <strong>將由本校負責主辦</strong>\r\n\r\n(4)   June - 認字比賽\r\n\r\n(5)   June - 畢業典禮\r\n\r\nBecause  of people like you, our vision and mission are possible. We truly  appreciate your thoughtfulness and want you to know that no matter how  much you choose to give, you are making a big difference for our school.  A bonus is that your gift may also qualify for a tax break for 2010  when you itemize deductions on your federal income tax return. We\'ll  issue a tax receipt to you for your contribution and also announce in  our weekly newsletter.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">元旦升旗典禮</span></strong>\r\n\r\n因響應全球同步升旗慶祝中華民國一百周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\r\n\r\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\r\n\r\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\r\n\r\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','publish','open','open','','mcs-newsletter-dec-18-2010','','','2010-12-16 18:10:45','2010-12-16 22:10:45','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=116',0,'post','',0),(117,1,'2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Szuping Lu\'s(呂思平) dedicated hard work. With his family support, we have very creative and unique reading month award this year.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Job Opportunity</span></strong>\n\nFord Powertrain Manufacturing Engineering has following jobs opening.\n\n1. Machining\n\n●Gears   ●Aluminum Machining   ●Tooling   ●Gauging\n\n2. Metallurgy\n\n3. Industrial / Plant Engineer\n\n●Industrial Engineer   ●Plant Layout   ●Material Handling\n\n4. Assembly and Test Engineer\n\nIf  you or you know of any talented people out there looking for work,  please direct them to the website to complete a career profile.\n\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings\" target=\"_blank\">http://corporate.ford.com/careers/north-american-careers/job-openings</a>:\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\n\nWe  have collected surveys from all classes and will review result with  each teacher individually to ensure the communication between teachers  and parents/students.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\n\nQQ bakery this week.  Please remember 3<sup>rd</sup> week each month, we will have QQ bakery sale as our fund raising.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Your Support Makes All The Difference</span></strong>\n\nBecause  of support received from you and other generous individuals, we have  been able to make real progress toward furthering our important mission.\n\nFor upcoming year, there are several major events:\n\n(1)   January – 新年晚會\n\n(2)   April - 校內演講比賽\n\n<strong>(3) </strong>May -校際演講比賽 – <strong>將由本校負責主辦</strong>\n\n(4)   June - 認字比賽\n\n(5)   June - 畢業典禮\n\nBecause  of people like you, our vision and mission are possible. We truly  appreciate your thoughtfulness and want you to know that no matter how  much you choose to give, you are making a big difference for our school.  A bonus is that your gift may also qualify for a tax break for 2010  when you itemize deductions on your federal income tax return. We\'ll  issue a tax receipt to you for your contribution and also announce in  our weekly newsletter.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">元旦升旗典禮</span></strong>\n\n因響應全球同步升旗慶祝中華民國一百周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\n\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\n\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\n\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\n\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','116-revision','','','2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','',116,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=117',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Happy New Year</span></strong>\r\n\r\nI hope all of you enjoyed the holiday break and spent some relaxing time with friends and family.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Communication</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAs  we discussed at beginning of school year, we would like to promote  email communication between teachers and parents/students so that we can  save paper and protect environment. Teachers will send out weekly  teaching progress and homework assignment by email. If you don’t have  computer to access these communication, you can stop by Madonna  University library during our regular school hours and there are many  computers available.\r\n\r\nWhile  I organized our school contact directory, I noticed that several  families were not on the weekly newsletter distribution list. If you  didn\'t receive our weekly newsletters in the past, you can go to school  website for archive information.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  had reviewed the survey result with each teacher individually on  12/18/2010. This survey served as a bridge between teachers and  parents/students and we will conduct another survey on later part of  this school year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Pre-Register for 2<sup>nd</sup> semester </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPre-register  for next semester will begin this week (1/8) and end on (1/15). You can  save $20.00 for each student, if you pre-register. It\'s school policy  that if you do not pre-register, <strong><em>you will be charged $20.00 registration fee for each student you enroll.</em></strong><strong> </strong>Registration form is attached and also available on school website.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011\r\n\r\nTickets on sale: 1/8/2011. Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Calendars</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  will have some 2011 calendars from Taiwan available this Saturday at  parents lounge. Limited quantity and first come first serve.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-8-2011','','','2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=118',0,'post','',0),(119,1,'2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','118-revision','','','2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','',118,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up the bakery from QQ bakery last week.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spring 2010-2011</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis  weekend will be the beginning of Spring 2010-2011 semester. Welcome  those new students and families. Because New Year Party is scheduled  next week, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">we will have after school curriculums this week for those who need more practice.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011 at 2:30 pm\r\n\r\nTickets on sale now: Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\nWe are highly encouraging all school members to invite friends and families to celebrate the year of rabbit.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party Last Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe will have one more meeting for all parents rep\'s from each class and staff this week to make sure we have everything covered.\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45pm','MCS Newsletter  Jan. 22, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-22-2011','','','2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=120',0,'post','',0),(121,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','','MCS Newsletter  ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','120-revision','','','2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','',120,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=121',0,'revision','',0),(122,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to purchase a copy of New Year Party DVD, please sign in this Saturday at Parent\'s Lounge. $5.00 only.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">張奶奶壓歲錢</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis will be distributed during class this Saturday. Students/Parents don\'t forget to thank 張奶奶\r\n\r\nnext time when you see her.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Academic Excellent Award</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom. Only for classes that teacher provided the list.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Spring After School Curriculum Registration</span></strong>\r\n\r\nRegistration will begin this week.','MCS Newsletter    Feb.5, 2011 ',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-5-2011','','','2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=122',0,'post','',0),(123,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:41','2011-02-04 01:27:41','<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\n\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\n\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\n\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&a